
mp4creator <options> mp4-file 
	-l 				// list track information
	-c <track-file> // create track from file
	-h [<track-id>]	// hint create track, or specified trackId
	-I				// interleave packets (audio tracks only)
	-p <payload-name>	// choose RTP payload format
	-d <track-id>	// delete trackid and any associated hint tracks
					// TBD delete associated data
	-O				// optimize
	-o 				// output file

TBD option to use an avi file as input


mp4encode becomes:
	mp4creator -c foo.divx -h foo.mp4
	mp4creator -c foo.mp3 -h -p 2250 foo.mp3 foo.mp4

Phlilips exercise becomes:
	mp4creator -t phlips.mp4
	mp4creator -h 3 -o hinted_philips.mp4 philips.mp4
	mp4creator -h 4 philips.mp4

avi to mp4 conversion:
	mp4creator -c foo.avi foo.mp4

isma compliance is automatic?

Creatable/Hintable types
.mp3
	RFC 2250 | RFC 3119
.aac
	ISMA
.divx | .mp4v
	RFC 3016

Per type
	virtual GetConfiguration
		list of name value pairs
	virtual GetSample

list track info
	MP4Read()
create and create and hint
	MP4Create() or MP4Clone() depending on if file already exists
hint
	MP4Clone()
delete track
	MP4Clone()
optimize
	MP4Optimize()
